@startuml Terminal State Management - Mode Transitions

title Terminal State Management - Mode Transitions and HITL Flow

package "TerminalMode State Machine" {
    enum TerminalMode {
        Normal
        ExecutingCommand
        WaitingLLM
        PromptingInstall
        AwaitingCommandApproval
        AwaitingAnswer
        AwaitingMoreInput(IncompleteReason)
    }

    state Normal as "Normal\n(Awaiting Input)"
    state ExecutingCommand as "ExecutingCommand\n(Running Shell Cmd)"
    state WaitingLLM as "WaitingLLM\n(Querying Backend)"
    state PromptingInstall as "PromptingInstall\n(Ask to Install)"
    state AwaitingApproval as "AwaitingCommandApproval\n(HITL: y/n)"
    state AwaitingAnswer as "AwaitingAnswer\n(HITL: Free Text)"
    state AwaitingMoreInput as "AwaitingMoreInput\n(Multiline Input)"

    [*] --> Normal

    Normal --> ExecutingCommand : User submits\nshell command
    Normal --> WaitingLLM : User submits\nnatural language
    Normal --> AwaitingMoreInput : Incomplete input\n(backslash, heredoc)
    Normal --> PromptingInstall : Command not found,\nask install (M2/M3)

    ExecutingCommand --> Normal : Command completes,\noutput processed
    ExecutingCommand --> AwaitingApproval : Shell confirmation\nneeded (rm -i, cp -i)
    ExecutingCommand --> AwaitingAnswer : Sudo password\nor confirmation

    WaitingLLM --> Normal : LLM returns\nresult/error
    WaitingLLM --> AwaitingApproval : LLM suggests\ncommand (needs y/n)
    WaitingLLM --> AwaitingAnswer : LLM asks\nquestion

    PromptingInstall --> Normal : User declines\ninstall
    PromptingInstall --> ExecutingCommand : User approves\ninstall, cmd runs (M2)

    AwaitingApproval --> ExecutingCommand : User presses 'y',\nexecute command
    AwaitingApproval --> Normal : User presses 'n',\ncancel command
    AwaitingApproval --> Normal : Cancel with Ctrl+C

    AwaitingAnswer --> Normal : User submits\nanswer
    AwaitingAnswer --> WaitingLLM : LLM resumes\nwith answer
    AwaitingAnswer --> ExecutingCommand : Shell prompt\nresponded

    AwaitingMoreInput --> Normal : User completes\nwith final Enter
    AwaitingMoreInput --> Normal : User cancels\nwith Ctrl+C
}

package "HITL Interaction Types" {
    class PendingInteraction {
        <<enum>>
        CommandApproval { command, message, confirmation_type }
        Question { question, options }
    }

    class ConfirmationType {
        <<enum>>
        RmWriteProtected
        RmInteractive { files, current_index, command }
        RmInteractiveBulk { file_count, is_recursive }
        CpInteractive { destination }
        MvInteractive { destination }
        LnInteractive { destination }
    }

    PendingInteraction --> ConfirmationType : may contain

    note right of PendingInteraction
        CommandApproval:
        - LLM wants to execute command
        - Shell confirmation (rm -i, etc)
        - Optional confirmation_type field

        Question:
        - LLM asking for clarification
        - Sudo password prompt
        - Free-form text response
    end note

    note right of ConfirmationType
        Distinguishes shell-originated
        confirmations from LLM-originated

        rm -i: per-file confirmation
        rm -I: bulk confirmation (>3 files)
        cp -i, mv -i, ln -i: overwrite
        rm on write-protected: force with -f
    end note
}

package "State Management Methods" {
    class TerminalState {
        + is_in_hitl_mode() -> bool
        + is_in_multiline_mode() -> bool
        + cancel_multiline()
        + get_multiline_input() -> String
        + enter_root_mode()
        + exit_root_mode()
        + is_root_mode() -> bool
        + start_throbber()
        + stop_throbber()
        + get_prompt_prefix() -> String
    }

    note right of TerminalState
        is_in_hitl_mode():
        Returns true if in AwaitingCommandApproval
        or AwaitingAnswer mode

        is_in_multiline_mode():
        Returns true if in AwaitingMoreInput
        with backslash continuation or heredoc

        cancel_multiline():
        Clears multiline_buffer and
        pending_heredoc, returns to Normal

        enter_root_mode() / exit_root_mode():
        Entered after "sudo su" or "su"
        Changes prompt symbol $ -> #

        start_throbber() / stop_throbber():
        Controls animation in WaitingLLM mode
        Shows braille animation in prompt

        get_prompt_prefix():
        Returns animated braille in WaitingLLM
        Returns static "|~|" otherwise
    end note
}

package "Prompt Generation" {
    class "Prompt Format" as PromptFormat {
        Format: |~| user@host:~/path$ [input]
        Format: |~| user@host:~/path# [input]  (root)
        Format: |⠘| user@host:~/path$ [input]  (WaitingLLM animated)
        ---
        Colors:
        Normal: Green
        ExecutingCommand: Yellow
        WaitingLLM: Blue
        Approval/Answer: Cyan
        MoreInput: Magenta
    }

    class "Root Mode" as RootMode {
        Triggered by:
        - "sudo su"
        - "su" or "su -"
        - Actual OS user = root (UID 0)
        ---
        Effects:
        - Prompt changes $ -> #
        - exit_root_mode() after exit cmd
    }

    note right of PromptFormat
        The |~| prefix is replaced with
        animated symbol during WaitingLLM:
        - |⠘| (frame 0)
        - |⠙| (frame 1)
        - |⠚| (frame 2)
        - |⠒| (frame 3)
        - cycles at 10 FPS

        Password mode replaces input
        with asterisks for display
    end note

    note right of RootMode
        User can enter root mode via:
        1. Interactive: "sudo su"
        2. Interactive: "su" / "su -"
        3. Automatic: libc::getuid() == 0

        Affects:
        - Prompt symbol only
        - Still shows colors
        - Can mix with WaitingLLM animation
    end note
}

package "Scroll State" {
    class ScrollbarInfo {
        - column: u16
        - height: u16
        - total_lines: usize
        - visible_lines: usize
        ---
        + is_on_scrollbar(col: u16) -> bool
        + row_to_scroll_position(row: u16) -> usize
    }

    note right of ScrollbarInfo
        Updated during render_frame()
        Used for mouse scrollbar interaction:

        row_to_scroll_position():
        - row 0 (top arrow) -> scroll to top
        - row height-1 (bottom) -> scroll bottom
        - row 1 to height-2 (track) -> proportional

        Mouse interaction:
        - MouseDown on scrollbar
        - MouseDrag during drag
        - MouseUp to finish
    end note
}

package "Input Buffer State" {
    class InputBuffer {
        - buffer: String
        - cursor_position: usize (in chars, not bytes)
        ---
        + insert_char(c: char)
        + delete_char()
        + move_cursor_left()
        + move_cursor_right()
        + clear()
        + set_text(text: String)
        + take() -> String
    }

    note right of InputBuffer
        Character-based cursor positions:
        - Handles Unicode correctly
        - Conversion to byte indices internal
        - Reset on clear() / take()
        - Positioned at end on set_text()
    end note
}

package "Command History State" {
    class CommandHistory {
        - history: Vec<String>
        - position: Option<usize>
        ---
        + add(command: String)
        + previous() -> Option<String>
        + next() -> Option<String>
        + reset_position()
    }

    note right of CommandHistory
        Arrow up/down navigation:
        - Up: moves to previous (older)
        - Down: moves to next (newer)
        - position = None means showing current
        - Skips empty/whitespace commands
        - Reset on submit_input()
    end note
}

package "Throbber Animation" {
    class ThrobberAnimator {
        - index: Arc<AtomicUsize>
        - active: Arc<AtomicBool>
        - thread_handle: Mutex<Option<JoinHandle>>
        ---
        + start()
        + stop()
        + is_running() -> bool
        + symbol() -> &'static str
    }

    note right of ThrobberAnimator
        Dedicated animation thread:
        - Spawned in start()
        - Updates index every 100ms (10 FPS)
        - Uses BRAILLE_DOUBLE symbols
        - Returns "~" when inactive

        Used in get_prompt_prefix():
        - Only shown when WaitingLLM mode
        - Cycles through 4 braille symbols
        - Smooth loading indicator
    end note
}

note bottom
    KEY DESIGN PATTERNS:

    1. STATE MACHINE: TerminalMode enum
       with clear transitions

    2. HITL FLOW: PendingInteraction
       separates approval (y/n) from
       questions (free text)

    3. SRP COMPOSITION: Separated buffers
       (Output, Input, History) composed
       in TerminalState

    4. ANIMATION THREAD: ThrobberAnimator
       runs independently, safe for
       concurrent access

    5. SCROLL SEPARATION: ScrollbarInfo
       tracks rendering state separately
       from OutputBuffer scroll position

    6. MULTILINE TRACKING: multiline_buffer
       and pending_heredoc for incomplete
       input continuation
end note

@enduml
